    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n```\n!!\n~\n~\n~\n~\n~\n~\n~\n~\n~\n~                                                   !!Nv\n~                                                   !!im\n[No Name]                             0,0-1          All\n!!:\n```\n`stc` affects displaying ui2 messages in `msg` area. \n\nNot sure how much it's an Nvim issue. Maybe partially it's a problem of statuscol.nvim defaults or user config (`ft_ignore = {'cmd', 'dialog', 'msg', 'pager'}` is a workaround). \n\n\ncc @luukvbaal \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nrequire('vim._core.ui2').enable({msg = {targets = {default = 'msg'}}})\n\nvim.o.cmdheight = 0\nprint('Nvim')\n\n-- minimized statuscol.nvim behavior\nfor _, win in ipairs(vim.api.nvim_tabpage_list_wins(0)) do\n  vim.api.nvim_set_option_value('stc', '!!', {win = win})\nend\n```\n\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo redundant line break in `msg`. Not sure what to do in `cmd`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-489+g228e6ca32a\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
